====Usage notes====
* In Old and Middle English, ''yes'' was a more forceful affirmative than {{m|en|yea}}.
* An example of '''yes''' used to disagree with a statement: the questions "You donâ€™t want it, do you?" and "Donâ€™t you want it?" are answered by "yes" if the respondent ''does'' want the item, and "no" if not. Many languages use a specific word for this purpose; see translation table below.
